{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"vegetable peeler, 12 hole muffin pan, parchment paper, rolling pin, pastry brush, oven","id":"r398049","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-hdg5CxN86Vg\/XZWfhJpdC3I\/AAAAAAAAfFw\/cY2um7JmHfEQwBQ_Xxr6ywhPN54mPfwmwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wJrNlLDOJf3Lqmmq.png","title":"Pear Apricot Roses","publishedAt":"2018-09-14T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"non-stick cooking spray"},{"content":"2 oz unsalted butter, cubed"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground cinnamon"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground nutmeg"},{"content":"8 oz dried apricots, pitted"},{"content":"8 oz sugar"},{"content":"1 lemon, thin peel only, no pith, plus 1 oz lemon juice"},{"content":"2 oz water"},{"content":"2 pears, quartered"},{"content":"1 package puff pastry, thawed per pkg. instructions"},{"content":"all-purpose flour, to dust"},{"content":"confectioners sugar, to garnish"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"44 g","calories":"1038 kJ \/ 248 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 400°F. Spray a 12 hole muffin pan with non-stick cooking spray."},{"content":"Place butter, cinnamon and nutmeg into mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/170°F\/speed <b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place apricots, sugar and lemon peel into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add lemon juice and water and cook <b>20 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b> then blend <b>40 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl, set aside and let cool to room temperature. Reserve half the cooled jam mixture for the recipe and transfer remaining jam to an airtight jar and refrigerate for another use."},{"content":"With a vegetable peeler, slice pears lengthwise into thin strips, transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Dust a large piece of parchment with flour. Transfer thawed puff pastry to prepared parchment and unroll. With a rolling pin, roll pastry to a ⅛ inch thickness. Cut into six strips (approx. 2 in. x 10 in.) Brush with reserved butter mixture, then with reserved apricot jam and top with a layer of sliced pears. Roll up the filled pastry and transfer each piece into a muffin hole with cut sides facing up. Repeat with remaining pastry creating 12 rosettes. Bake for 35-40 minutes (400°F) or until golden brown. Dust with confectioners sugar and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Thaw and store puff pastry in refrigerator in its original sealed package: when you come home from the store, refrigerate puff pastry instead of freezing.","Thaw and use at room temperature: allow puff pastry to thaw in packaging at room temperature according to package directions. Do not open until all other ingredients are assembled and you are ready to work."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","12 portions"]}